    h4 Datto
      span.section-annotation May-Aug 2019
    h6 Software Engineering Intern
    p The main product I worked on at Datto is called SaaS protection which backs up GSuite and O365. I worked on adding new features into the application as well as fixing issues that were directly affecting customer backups. I touched each major part of the codebase including a Rails application, a PHP Symfony API, and a collection of akka microservices written in Scala.
    p There was an intern hackathon over 2 days where we were given 12 hours each day to build anything that we wanted for the company. The team I was on built an application to detect when the snack bins were empty and create a JIRA ticket automiatcally. Someone on my team had a great idea to put QR codes on the bottom of the bin and so then if they could be seen we'd know that the bin is empty. We used a raspberry pi with a camera attached to it to take pictures of the bins and detect the QR codes in them. Then the device reported back to a flask web API which is the part that I worked on. We also had a web application that showed you all the statuses of the snack bins and the most recent pictures that were taken of them. 
    p They hired outside professionals to train us on both the PHP framework Symfony and the Scala framework akka. The Symfony training was held by Ryan Weaver who is the lead writer for their documentation. He went over the container/services, auto-wiring, and authentication all while walking us through building a simple web application. The akka training was held by Daniel Cioc√Ærlan who is an instructor on Udemy. He went over functional programming basics, the Scala type system, akka actors, akka streams, and gave us exercises to help us learn the concepts.
