    h4.mt-4 EagleView
      span.section-annotation Jan-Aug 2018
    h6 Software Engineering Co-Op
    p I worked on a scrum team of about 10 people developing a web application for viewing pictures of the earth taken from airplanes. It's similar to Google Earth except the images are much higher quality since they're taken from a lower level than satellites. We used a micro-service architecture so that other applications could easily re-use functionality we developed for the primary product. My team also maintained a couple internal applications that were used by other people in the company to help them capture the images and process them.
    p During my time there I worked on almost every project that my team managed so I learned many different code-bases during my time there. I worked on SPAs, regular websites, and APIs. I also worked with Jenkins and Docker to help improve my team's development process. I laid the groundwork for a new micro-service for my team written in Go. I set up a containerized application with a couple sample endpoints, Swagger docs, and created jenkins jobs to deploy it to a test and staging environment.
